    narr:narration """This hub maintains the project's controlled vocabulary, establishing a canonical lexicon for [narrative architecture](narr:StyleObs_KeyPhrase_NarrArch) and [collective memory](narr:StyleObs_CollectiveMemoryTerm). The terminology is anchored by core positioning phrases like [IP-as-code](narr:Observation_IPAsCode) and [Collaborative Worldview](narr:StyleObs_TerminologyControl_IPasCode), which enforce a [terminology-control rule](narr:StyleObs_TerminologyControl) prioritizing specific metaphors over generic industry labels. The vocabulary extends into coined metaphors that define the system's stance on data management, specifically [context squishing](narr:Observation_ContextSquishing) versus [intentional memory](narr:Observation_IntentionalMemory), and the [cultivation trap](narr:Observation_CultivationTrap) of lock-in. Technical abstractions are formalized through the [git-native triad](narr:Observation_GitNativeTriad) and precise definitions for [Memory](narr:Obs_MemoryDefinition) and [Transaction](narr:Obs_TransactionDefinition). The span includes operational shorthand like [SSoT](narr:StyleObs_7) and [product market fit](narr:StyleObs_KeyPhrase_PMF), alongside structural terms like [compiled target](narr:Observation_CompiledTarget) and [tool signatures](narr:StyleObs_TechTerms), which together frame the project's technical and strategic identity.""" ;
